<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880830-0127 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Magma Copper Names Aide at BP Minerals To Two Top Posts </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS MGCP BP </CO><DATELINE> SAN MANUEL, Ariz.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Magma Copper Co. named J. Burgess Winter, a former executive at British Petroleum's U.S. minerals unit, as its president and chief executive officer.    As chief executive, Mr. Winter, 55 years old, succeeds Magma's chairman, Donald J. Donahue, who held the chief executive's title on an interim basis since April, following the death of Brian R. Woolfe, who had served as president and chief executive of the copper producer. Mr. Donahue remains chairman.    As president, Mr. Winter succeeds John R. Parry, a director who held the president's title on an interim basis. Mr. Winter also was named a director of Magma.    Mr. Winter previously was vice president-operations of the mineral group of BP Minerals America, a unit of London-based British Petroleum.    Prior to joining BP Minerals America, which previously was Kennecott Minerals, Mr. Winter was vice president and general manager of Inspiration Consolidated Copper Co., Miami, Ariz., from 1976 to 1983. Before that, he spent 24 years in technical and operations management posts with Anglo America Corp. of South Africa. </TEXT></DOC>